The young Czechs get drunk with Fernet and rum. Beer is no longer in shape, because it works slowly.
Fernet, rum, vodka and even good whiskeys stolen from their parents.
These are the drinks that cause young drinkers to end up in medical care at less than 15 years of age.
Children who end up lying in the hospital continuously to overcome the hangover are no longer an exception.
This derives from the experience of doctors who encounter such cases in hospital pediatric admissions.
"Drinking beer or wine is no longer fashionable, because it takes a long time to get them drunk."
