It is precisely the lack of interest of parents or even their clear tolerance for drinking on the part of their children that is considered to be the main cause of the increase in alcohol consumption among young people.
The experts point out that, in the case of children, one cannot speak properly of dependence.
"Alcohol means a person who has had a chronic dependence on alcohol for several years, with all the phenomena associated with alcohol, which does not occur in children."
"In those who drink alcohol repeatedly, rather it is due to a systematically failed social or family environment," explains Chief Pelikán.
According to the spokesman Jurinová, this year at Motol's pediatric clinic, forty drunk children were hospitalized until mid-November.
