"I have often used the cost as a means of educating them, when on the visit I tell children how much their drunkenness has cost and they would have to spend all summer in a youth job to earn enough to pay for themselves that night," Pelikán adds.
Medical insurance, in your opinion, perhaps as a retrogressive measure, which usually returns people the costs of treatment, does not do so in the case of children who drink.
