One of the most provocative states that the intense reports on the process, including the widespread use of Twitter by mass media journalists, created "an atmosphere of circus", and such widespread and immediate saturation with exhilarating details caused public passions to exert inappropriate influence on the jury.
The complaint could force appellate judges to deal with the question of whether the new technology requires new rules in the courtroom.
